<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Algo stablecoin!</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Two weeks ago an algorithmic stablecoi=
n called TerraUSD (or UST) blew up, incinerating tens of billions of dollar=
s of market value. The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/27811549.267618/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjItMDUtMTEvdGVycmEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyMzIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX=
21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNTIzJnV0bV9j=
YW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4cbb77f5" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> idea o=
f an algorithmic stablecoin</a> is that it should always be worth a dollar =
because of an arbitrage mechanism in which one stablecoin can always be exc=
hanged for a number of units of some other crypto token =E2=80=94=C2=A0for =
TerraUSD, it was called Luna =E2=80=94=C2=A0with a market value of $1. If t=
hat other token (Luna) is worth $100 or $10 or $1 or $0.10, that works fine=
; if the stablecoin trades below $1, you buy it for $0.97 or whatever and r=
edeem it for some Luna that you can sell for a dollar, making an arbitrage =
profit and pushing the price of the stablecoin back to $1.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">The problem is twofold. One is that, if people want to rede=
em a lot of the stablecoin, the algorithm will print a lot of the other tok=
en (Luna), which will tend to drive down the price of that token, which mig=
ht undermine confidence in the stablecoin, which might lead to more redempt=
ions, which will lead to more printing, which will drive down the price, et=
c., in what is called a =E2=80=9Cdeath spiral.=E2=80=9D This is a very well=
-known problem that long predates crypto; companies have for years issued b=
onds that are convertible into fixed dollar amounts of stock, which are cal=
led =E2=80=9Cdeath-spiral convertibles=E2=80=9D and have the same problem. =
The other problem that is more specific to crypto is that the other token =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0Luna =E2=80=94=C2=A0is just made up, and its value is tied t=
o confidence in the stablecoin. If a death spiral starts, there is nothing =
to underpin the value of that token,=C2=A0so it can go to zero fast. Luna w=
as trading in the $80s in early May; it=E2=80=99s at <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27811549.267618/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2lubWFya2V0=
Y2FwLmNvbS9jdXJyZW5jaWVzL3RlcnJhLWx1bmEv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7b409f60"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">about $0.0002</a> today. TerraUSD is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/27811549.267618/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2lubWFya2V0Y2FwLmN=
vbS9jdXJyZW5jaWVzL3RlcnJhdXNkLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB26ffb421" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
